      "side": 1,
      "message": "During review of PKCE support for new `DiscoveryOAuthService`, see change 564242, that referenced SAP IAS implementation in the commit message:\n\n\n```\nAdd PKCE support according to the same change for SAP IAS.\n```\n\nI noticed a significant concurrency issue in the implementation of `SAPIasOAuthService` that will cause authentication failures under concurrent load.\n\nIn Gerrit, these service classes are singletons. The current patch stores `authorizationUrlBuilder` as a final field in the singleton and calls `initPKCE()` on it inside `getAuthorizationUrl()`. Because this builder is shared across all users, one user\u0027s login request will overwrite the `code_verifier` for another user currently in the middle of a login flow.\n\n**The Failure Scenario**\n\n* User A starts login -\u003e initPKCE() sets Verifier X.\n* User B starts login -\u003e initPKCE() overwrites with Verifier Y.\n* User A returns from the IDP -\u003e getAccessToken() fetches the shared Verifier Y (instead of X).\n\n**Result**\n\nThe IDP rejects the token exchange because the verifier doesn\u0027t match the original challenge.\n\n**Resolution**\n\nTo fix this, the `code_verifier` must be treated as request-scoped data. I have addressed this in two steps:\n\n* change 564343: Extends the Gerrit Extension API to support PKCE by introducing `OAuthAuthorizationInfo`. This allows Gerrit to safely persist the verifier in the user\u0027s session. Note that `OAuthSession` has request scope.\n* change 564344: Updates the SAPIAS provider to use this new API, removing the shared state from the singleton and ensuring thread-safe authentication. I also added the tests, which were completely missing.",
